article.headline: Alabama 75, Tennessee St. 66
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. -- Alonzo Gee scored 24 points and Alabama defeated Tennessee State 75-66 on Wednesday night. It was the fifth-straight game that Gee led the Crimson Tide (6-3) in scoring. Yamene Coleman added 14 points and a career-high 13 rebounds and Ronald Steele scored 13 points for Alabama. For Tennessee State (3-6) Gerald Robinson had 15 points, Darius Cox scored 14 and Parker Smith added 10. After falling behind 4-2 early, Alabama led the rest of the way. The Crimson Tide took their biggest lead of the game with 1:30 left in the first half as Coleman hit a jump hook for a 39-17 advantage. With 12:46 left to play, Tennessee State brought the score to 54-40 on a layup by Robinson, but that was as close as the Tigers would get as Alabama responded with five unanswered points to push the lead to 54-50 with 9:49 remaining.
